The buildings were collectively branded as the \"Tundra Trio\", and were renovated as upscale properties that can be rented for events.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.sportsbusinessdaily.com/Journal/Issues/2014/08/11/Facilities/Tundra-Trio.aspx|title=Refined hospitality, just a Lambeau leap away|website=Sports Business Journal|language=en|access-date=2018-07-27}}</ref>\n\nIn 2013, GKB station [[WKNR]] ESPN 850 in Cleveland became the AM [[flagship station]] for the [[Cleveland Browns]].<ref>[http://www.allaccess.com/net-news/archive/story/116830/cleveland-browns-moving-to-92-3-the-fan-wknr-wncx- WKNR becomes Browns AM flagship - All Access.com]</ref>\n\nIn 2012, GKB further branched out into the field of retail, opening the first of what is currently a chain of three [[Verizon Wireless]] stores in Wisconsin, and one in [[New York City]].<ref name = \"GKB's roots\" /><ref>[http://goodkarmabrands.com/wireless/store-locations GKB Wireless - Good Karma Brands.com]</ref>\n\nIn January 2014, to reflect the company's brand extension, GKB officially changed its name from Good Karma Broadcasting to its current name of Good Karma Brands.\n\nOn July 17, 2014, it was reported that GKB had purchased a minority ownership stake in the [[Milwaukee Bucks]] of the [[National Basketball Association]] (NBA).<ref>[http://fox6now.com/2014/07/16/approved-nba-okays-list-of-new-milwaukee-bucks-minority-owners-but-whos-on-that-list GKB buys stake in Bucks - Fox 6 Now.com]</ref>\n\nOn July 27, 2018, GKB announced it had reached a deal to acquire [[WTMJ (AM)|WTMJ]] and [[WKTI]] in Milwaukee from the [[E. W. Scripps Company]]. The company had acquired the stations through its purchase of [[Journal Media Group|Journal Communications]], but had later chosen to exit the radio business.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.rbr.com/good-karma-pays-off-for-craig-karmazin/|title=Good Karma Pays Off For Craig Karmazin |website=Radio & Television Business Report|language=en-US|access-date=2018-07-27}}</ref> WKTI would flip to ESPN Radio.<ref name=\"mjs-wvtycountry\">{{cite news |last1=Foran |first1=Chris |title=Radio station switches back to country after WKTI makes move to an all-sports format |url=https://www.jsonline.com/story/entertainment/television-radio/2018/10/31/radio-station-switches-back-country-after-wkti-shifts-all-sports/1836041002/ |date=October 31, 2018 |accessdate=November 1, 2018 |work=[[Milwaukee Journal Sentinel]] |language=en}}</ref>\n\nOn August 28, 2019, it was announced by ESPN Radio that day-to-day management of [[Chicago]]'s [[WMVP]] would move from direct purview by ESPN to a management agreement with Good Karma Brands. The current general manager, Jim Pastor, will retire at the end of the year, with Good Karma expected to begin operating the station on September 29, 2019 under a lease with Disney (no information about a conversion to an eventual station purchase has been revealed). No changes to personnel and facilities in the near future are currently expected under the lease agreement.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.robertfeder.com/2019/08/28/new-management-team-brings-good-karma-take-espn-1000/|title=New management team brings Good Karma to take over ESPN 1000|last=Feder|first=Robert|date=28 August 2019|accessdate=29 August 2019}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.bizjournals.com/milwaukee/news/2019/08/28/milwaukees-good-karma-agrees-to-run-chicago-espn.html|title=Milwaukee's Good Karma agrees to run Chicago ESPN radio station|last=Kirchen|first=Rich|date=28 August 2019|work=[[American City Business Journals|The Business Journal of Milwaukee]]|accessdate=29 August 2019}}</ref>\n\n==List of radio stations==\n\n===Florida===\n'''West Palm Beach'''\n*[[WEFL]]/760: Sports ([[TUDN Radio|TUND)]]\n*[[WUUB]]/106.3: Sports ([[ESPN Radio|ESPN]])\n\n===Illinois===\n'''Chicago'''\n*[[WMVP]]/1000: Sports (ESPN) (managed by Good Karma Brands, owned by [[The Walt Disney Company]])\n\n===Ohio===\n'''Cleveland'''\n*[[WKNR]]/850: Sports (ESPN)\n*[[WWGK]